Christa S. Quarles CFA: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 7:23 AM ET
Internet and Direct Marketing Retail

Company Overview of The Priceline Group Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Christa S. Quarles CFAChief Executive Officer of Opentable, Inc., The Priceline Group Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 6 different industries.See Board Relationships43--
Background

		Ms. Christa S. Quarles, CFA, has been the Chief Executive Officer of OpenTable, Inc. at The Priceline Group Inc. since November 17, 2015. Ms. Quarles served as an Interim Chief Executive Officer and Chief Financial Officer of OpenTable, Inc. until November 17, 2015. She leads the global business strategy and vision for OpenTable. She served as the Chief Business Officer for Nextdoor.com, Inc., where she oversaw finance, business intelligence, HR, business development ... and legal. She served as the Chief Financial Officer of Playdom, Inc., since December 2009 and served as its Vice President. She joined Playdom in December 2009. She served as the Senior Vice President and General Manager at Disney, where she led the Mobile and Social Games divisions within The Walt Disney Company. She joined Disney in 2010 as part of the acquisition of Playdom, where she served as Chief Financial Officer. In her career, she spent ten years as an Equity Research Analyst covering the Internet sector at Thomas Weisel Partners (now Stifel Financial) and served as its Managing Director in the Equity Research Group. She served as Managing Director and Senior Equity Research Analyst of Thomas Weisel Partners Equity Research. She covered the Internet sector at the Thomas Weisel Partners since 2000. As the lead Internet Analyst, she was responsible for developing the Thomas Weisel Partners's research themes and conducts proprietary research on the dynamics of the secular shifts of interactive advertising and media consumption. She served as Managing Director of Thomas Weisel Partners Group. Prior to Thomas Weisel, she served as a Summer Associate at Morgan Stanley Investment Management analyzing media stocks. Prior to that, she served as an Assistant Vice President and Equity Analyst at BofA Merrill Lynch, Research Division, where she worked in the Fixed-Income Research Department analyzing bond portfolios for institutional accounts. She has been an Independent Director of Kimberly-Clark Corporation since June 15, 2016. She was recognized by Greenwich Associates, Forbes and Starmine for her work in the space. She holds a CFA designation. Ms. Quarles graduated with a B.S. in Economics and German from Carnegie Mellon University, where she graduated first in the Department of Economics, received university and college honors and was named to Phi Beta Kappa. She also holds an M.B.A. from the Harvard Business School.Read Full Background




